The novella "'''Side Trip'''" was the first collaboration between [[Timothy Zahn]] and [[Michael A. Stackpole]]. The novella consists of four parts, parts one and four being written by Zahn and parts two and three written by Stackpole. Parts one and two were originally published in the [[Star Wars Adventure Journal 12|''Star Wars Adventure Journal'' 12]] by [[West End Games]] in [[February]] [[1997]] and parts three and four were originally published in [[Star Wars Adventure Journal 13|''Star Wars Adventure Journal'' 13]] by West End Games in [[May]] 1997. The full story was later compiled in the Short Story Anthology ''[[Tales from the Empire]]'' which was published by [[Bantam Spectra]] in [[November]] 1997. It was also available online via [[Hyperspace: The Official Star Wars Fan Club|Hyperspace]].

==Plot summary==
[[Merchant/Legends|Traders]] [[Haber Trell]] and [[Maranne Darmic]] and their [[Freighter/Legends|freighter]] the ''[[Hopskip]]'' carrying [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]] [[Smuggler/Legends|contraband]], is intercepted by the [[Imperial-class Star Destroyer/Legends|Imperial Star Destroyer]] ''[[Admonitor]]''. Its smuggler crew is not subjected to inspection, but is rather forced by [[Captain/Legends|Captain]] [[Dagon Niriz|Niriz]] to take aboard [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunter]] [[Jodo Kast]], who supervises them on an [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] assignment. They are to deliver a cargo to [[Corellia/Legends|Corellia]]. 

Following Kast's bewildering instructions, the crew draws the attention of [[Black Sun/Legends|Black Sun]] [[Crime lord/Legends|criminals]], as well as [[Corellian Security Force]] agents [[Hal Horn|Hal]] and [[Corran Horn/Legends|Corran Horn]]. The Horns, posing as traders, agree to help the ''Hopskip'' crew, but Hal and half the crew – Captian Trell and [[Rathe Palror]] – are kidnapped by Black Sun. Kast agrees to help Corran free them. Kast's mercurial actions are part of an elaborate plot to set up Black Sun mobster [[Zekka Thyne]] for a fall. Corran is able to free his [[Parent/Legends|father]] as well as the captive ''Hopskip'' crewers and capture Thyne. 

Imperial [[Stormtrooper/Legends|stormtroopers]] led by [[Colonel/Legends|Colonel]] [[Maximilian Veers/Legends|Veers]], tipped off that Thyne is harboring Rebel contraband, attack Thyne's compound. The ''Hopskip'' crew, meanwhile, return to the [[Hyperspace route/Legends|space lanes]], none the wiser that their original cargo has been fitted with Imperial [[Homing beacon/Legends|tracking devices]], which will lead the Empire to [[Derra IV/Legends|Derra IV]]. The disruption in Black Sun operations is meant to create a distracting grievance for [[Prince/Legends|Prince]] [[Xizor/Legends|Xizor]] – something that pleases [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader]]. He thanks Kast – or, rather, the genius Imperial tactician hiding behind the [[Mandalorian armor/Legends|Mandalorian armor]]: [[Grand Admiral/Legends|Grand Admiral]] [[Mitth'raw'nuruodo/Legends|Thrawn]]. His victory also gains the [[Chiss/Legends|Chiss]] Admiral a substantial favor from Darth Vader: command of his [[Noghri Death Commando|Noghri Death Commandos]].

==Continuity==
Between the events in this short story and the novel ''[[Choices of One]]'' ([[2011]]), it would appear that the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Empire]] owed its triumph at the [[Battle of Hoth/Legends|Battle of Hoth]] in [[Star Wars: Episode V The Empire Strikes Back|''The Empire Strikes Back'']] ([[1980]]) to [[Grand Admiral/Legends|Grand Admiral]] [[Mitth'raw'nuruodo/Legends|Thrawn]]. It was his handiwork that narrowed the search for the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel]] base to [[Water/Legends|ice]] [[Planet/Legends|planets]], his intelligence that led to the disastrous defeat at [[Derra IV/Legends|Derra IV]] that ensured the [[Hoth/Legends|Hoth]] Rebels would be ill equipped, and his recommendation to [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Vader]] to place [[Maximilian Veers/Legends|Veers]] in command of his ground forces. In exchange, Thrawn was given access to Vader's [[Noghri Death Commando|Noghri death commandos]], who were not described in this story but would figure prominently in the [[Star Wars: The Thrawn Trilogy|''Thrawn Trilogy'']] ([[1991]]-[[1993]]).<ref name="TERC" />

